The current program uses PathPlanner for alignment and only has a start and end waypoint. Previously, I tried setting the end rotation to match the robot’s current heading (to avoid rotating), and it moved smoothly in a straight line.

Now, I want to include rotation in the alignment as well.

However, the problem is that I can’t figure out which part of the code is causing issues.

I’m hoping someone more experienced can help point me in the right direction

We are using apriltag2 command btw
